Package network.Socket

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClientLauncherSocket  
    CommandLauncherProxySocket
    This class behave like a command Container, but instead of adding a command in a pool, sends it to the executor on the server
    CommandReceiverSocket
    A CommandReceiverSocket is an object placed in the server side of the application that receives a command through the net and add it to a command Launcher.
    JsonReceiverProxySocket
    Placed on the server side, pretends to be a jsonReceiver, but sends the json to the corresponding client
    JsonRouterSocket
    The socket class that receives from the network the response of the commands
    SocketServer
    Accept socket connections
